{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6720609f-7500-4a52-80d7-57d27a72ee26","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for the Testing Platform works by running the test project as an executable. With `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package installed, you start it like this:\n\n```\ndotnet run -- --hotreload\n```\n\n`dotnet test` does **not** support the `--hotreload` flag. The hot reload extension requires the Testing Platform's direct execution mode, which is what `dotnet run` provides.\n\nMake sure you also have the environment variable `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED` set to `1` if required by your version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ed7a1529-42b0-4e1a-8c3d-7a66f3fa5da8","outputTokens":163,"requestId":"A03F:28C8F:1A63CAB:1DDD1CE:69FE9161"},"id":"f6ce767c-3dce-451d-b6bc-784cbf5c10db","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:44:06.556Z","parentId":"2985a9bb-ec2e-42eb-9ca5-c4f00cf5a1e1"}
